<h1>Alex Jerez</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://alexjerez.net/now/">alexjerez.net/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Huntington
NY
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Visual Artist, Programmer and Musician
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I create things. sometimes on a computer, other times with my hands.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Because I enjoy it. If you can make a living doing what you enjoy, you're on a good track.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
"If you're unsure of something, meditate on it. Whether that means sitting cross-legged with your eyes closed, going for a walk, or drawing a picture.  Sometimes you already know the answer, but your mind is too full to think clearly."
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
'Steal Like an Artist' by @austinkleon - A short but very inspiring read.  'How to Win Friends and Influence People' by Dale Carnegie - One of the original manuals for success. Read by a large number of successful people including Warren Buffet and Howard Stern
</p>

